### Artemis Compatibility — Breaking Changes

The Artemis host application requires patching to match the new Sneeze API:

- `SNEEZE_HOST` now implements `ISNEEZE` (only `Log()` callback, engine-level config: `sAppDataPath`, `sSessionPath`, `sRenderer`).
- New `VIEWPORT_HOST` class implements `IVIEWPORT` (per-window: `pNativeWindow`, `nWidth`, `nHeight`, `OnFrameReady()`, optional inspector callbacks).
- Engine lifecycle: `SNEEZE engine(pHost)` -> `engine.Initialize()` -> `engine.OpenViewport(pViewportHost, sUrl)` -> loop -> `engine.CloseViewport(pVP)` -> `engine.Shutdown()`.
- Input via `pViewport->SetMouseInput()` / `SetKeyInput()` instead of `pSneeze->SetMouseInput()`.
- Framebuffer via `pViewport->LockFrameBuffer()` / `UnlockFrameBuffer()` instead of `pSneeze->LockFrameBuffer()`.
- `pSneeze->GetHost()` -> `pSneeze->Host()`.

